<TEXT>
President Clinton is calling for a crackdown on drunk drivers.
In his <TIMEX2 val="XXXX-WXX" mod="" set="YES" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">weekly</TIMEX2> radio address <TIMEX2 val="1998-12-26" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">today</TIMEX2>, he urged adoption of a national blood
alcohol limit, 0.08%.
<TIMEX2 val="1998" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">This year</TIMEX2> I worked with members of Congress to make 0.08 the law of the
land.
Tragically the special interests blocked this life saving measure.
I am determined to succeed in setting a 0.08 standard in <TIMEX2 val="1999" mod="" set="" non_specific="" anchor_val="" anchor_dir="" comment="">the new year</TIMEX2>.
<TURN>
Most states aren't as tough and have a higher legal limit than that.
